foremost abou</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">t securing the quality of teaching through improved leadership and management. This can be achieved through school to school support and collaboration. The latter can be tailor made to each school, if local solutions are found. However, a culture of compet</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ition between schools and worki</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ng in silos has been engendered, that prevents a readiness to help a neighbouring institution at the expense of one’s own.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>